    originStory: `Raised below the poverty line in the north of England, Natalie craved freedom of time, money and choice from young and experimented with online businesses as a teenager. Her first hit, Oh My Glow, grew fast but hit cash-flow crises and crushing isolation — she did it all alone with no mentors. That loneliness was the seed: she figured there had to be other women like her, so she started a community to bring in the mentors they all wanted. That became BossBabe. The gut-punch second act: the company she built to give women freedom quietly became a cage for HER. Motherhood, burnout and a painful co-founder exit forced her to slow down, and she realised the freedom BossBabe preached was no longer how it actually ran. So she rebuilt it to scale without her at the centre — and that renovation became the Freedom-Based Business Method she now teaches.`,
