    originStory: `Wineland grew up WITHOUT a healthy masculine role model. His mother's Buddhist practice put spirituality in front of him early, and it was through those spiritual circles that he met his first real male mentor — a turning point that seeded his life's work on healthy masculine leadership. The professional origin is a classic apprentice-to-master arc: he became a devoted student of David Deida ("The Way of the Superior Man") and Michaela Boehm, apprenticed for years assisting and leading their men's practices, then founded The New Men's Work Project in 2014 to carry the work at scale. The emotional hook: a boy with no template for manhood grows up to become the man who hands hundreds of thousands of men their missing template. He is candid that this is a practice "filled with failure and recommitment," not a one-time awakening, and openly builds on Deida's lineage rather than claiming to have originated polarity theory.`,
    framework: {
      name: `Embodied Presence / Masculine-Feminine Polarity (the "From The Core" method)`,
      summary: `The teachable core: every human carries both a masculine energetic (stillness, depth, direction) and a feminine energetic (flow, radiance, change), regardless of biological sex, and attraction and intimacy run on the POLARITY between them. Wineland's contribution is making "presence" physical and trainable rather than mystical. The practice is nervous-system-level: slow the breath, drop the voice, open the chest, ground through the root, and "feel your partner better than they can feel themselves." His line: "When your root is awake and your heart is open, you become impossible to ignore, and safe to trust." The aim is a man leading "from his core" (root + heart) instead of from ego, strategy or numbness. The forthcoming "Evolutionary Love" packages the relational version as four pillars: inner work, devotion to love's field, intimacy mastery, erotic artistry.`,
    },
    paperWall: `The inherited paradigm of masculinity — strength as stoicism, dominance, self-sufficiency, NOT needing anyone — is broken, and it has harmed women, the planet and men themselves. Wineland's counter-belief: the strongest, most attractive thing a man can do is FEEL more, not armour up. "There is no true masculinity without the integration of the feminine." Two spikier walls: (1) "Do your healing first, then show up" is a trap — action precedes perfect readiness, and you heal by leading, not by waiting to be fixed. (2) In a relationship the feminine partner has to RELAX her leadership for polarity and desire to ignite — a genuinely provocative claim in 2026 that he frames energetically, not politically. He also insists emotional intelligence is not innate — it is "an awareness practice" that can be trained like a muscle.`,
    clipMoments: [
      `The reveal that the most desirable trait in a man is not confidence or success but the capacity to FEEL — and that feeling can be trained like a bicep: "emotional intelligence is really just an awareness practice."`,
      `The nervous-system mechanics of attraction as a physical instruction: "The slower your breath, the slower your talk, the deeper your voice, the more women feel your depth, and that nourishes their nervous system." A do-it-right-now moment.`,
      `The contrarian bomb: "Women want men who don't need them but desire them deeply." Plus the claim that the feminine can only relax when the masculine truly leads.`,
      `The origin gut-punch: a boy with zero healthy male role models becomes the teacher who has handed hundreds of thousands of men theirs — and the admission that intimacy is "a practice filled with failure and recommitment."`,
    ],
    questions: {
      coldOpen: [
        `You teach that the strongest thing a man can do is feel MORE, not less. Most men were raised to believe the exact opposite. Which one of them is going to break first — them, or you?`,
        `You grew up without a single healthy example of a man. So where did you get the blueprint you now hand to hundreds of thousands of them?`,
      ],
      act1_origin: [
        `You had no healthy masculine role model growing up. Take me to the moment you realised that hole was going to become your life's work, not just your wound.`,
        `You spent years as the apprentice — assisting David Deida and Michaela Boehm, carrying the bags, leading their rooms. What did you learn standing in the master's shadow that you could never have learned as the teacher?`,
        `There's a moment every student has to leave the lineage and risk their own voice. Deida already said the big things about polarity. What did you know you had to add — or that you thought he got wrong?`,
        `You trained in business — Keith Cunningham, Chet Holmes — before you ever taught intimacy. How much of turning this into a movement was spiritual, and how much was pure operator?`,
      ],
      act2_blueprint: [
        `Let's name it. Every human has a masculine energetic and a feminine energetic. Give me the definition of "presence" that a skeptic in the back row could actually practice tonight.`,
        `You say a man should "feel his partner better than she can feel herself." Walk me through the actual reps — breath, voice, posture, root. Don't tell me the philosophy, give me the drill.`,
        `Your line is "when your root is awake and your heart is open, you become impossible to ignore, and safe to trust." Those usually cancel out. How does one practice produce both?`,
        `The new book, Evolutionary Love, has four pillars. If a couple could only install ONE this week to change everything, which pillar — and why that one?`,
      ],
      act3_paperwall: [
        `You say the feminine can only relax when the masculine leads. In 2026 that sentence gets you cancelled in some rooms. Defend it — and tell me what people hear that you're NOT saying.`,
        `You tell men NOT to wait until they're healed to show up and lead. Every therapist on the internet says the opposite. Why is "heal first" actually the trap?`,
        `The old model of masculinity — stoic, dominant, needs no one — you say it harmed women, the planet, and men themselves. Who profits from keeping that broken model alive?`,
        `You claim emotional intelligence is a trainable skill, not a personality trait. So "men just aren't wired for feelings" isn't biology, it's a choice. Say that to the man hiding behind it.`,
      ],
      curveball: [
        `You've stood in front of thousands of men and helped them feel. When was the last time YOUR own root shut down and your heart closed — in your own marriage? What did you do?`,
        `If everything you teach could be reduced to one sentence carved above every man's door, what does it say?`,
        `You want 1,000 men's groups on Earth. Say it's 100 years from now and it worked — every man was raised in this. What's the FIRST problem in the world that quietly disappears?`,
      ],
    },
    vishenNotes: `ACCURACY FLAGS: an "L.I.F.E. Method" / "Self-Liberation Blueprint" surfaced on ONE aggregator page and could NOT be corroborated — do NOT assert these on air. His real, defensible named work is masculine/feminine POLARITY + EMBODIED PRESENCE ("From The Core"), with the forthcoming four-pillar "Evolutionary Love." Book isn't out yet — treat pillars as pre-release. He is emphatically DERIVATIVE of David Deida and says so — this is a FEATURE for Scaling Wisdom: he's the guy who turned a mystic's ideas into a scalable, teachable method. Don't let him hide behind Deida; push him to own his specific contribution. EXTRACTOR: he speaks in soft, therapeutic cadence — keep pulling him from "philosophy" to "give me the drill." Most polarizing, clip-worthy line: "the feminine can only relax when the masculine leads" — handle Act 3 there, and press him on what he's NOT saying so it can't be quote-mined into a gender-war clip.`,
