    vishenNotes: `STRONG fit — three near-death arcs give the emotional contrast Scaling Wisdom prizes, and the affirmations takedown is a ready-made Act 3 paper wall. Lean into the reframe that the movement was born from DEBT AND DEPRESSION (2008), not the crash — the counter-intuitive beat most interviewers miss, and it sets up "wisdom-into-movement" better than the crash. ACCURACY FLAGS: creation date varies (2007/2008; book 2012) — let him state it. Book stats drift (1M vs 2M+ copies, 34 vs 37 languages) — let him quote his own. "650 hours of chemo" / "clinically dead 6 minutes" are his own well-documented retellings — don't over-precision them. His cancer approach mixed chemo with holistic protocols — sensitive; frame as HIS choice, avoid anything reading as medical advice or endorsing alternatives over treatment. Affirmations quote is verbatim-close from his Entrepreneur article. House-style hooks: DEBT ties to money, cancer to health, his suicidal-ideation candor to relationship-with-self.`,
